      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): reject invalid search limit values",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- reject malformed `--limit` values for `plugins search` and `skills search`\n- keep the strict positive-integer option adapter in a Commander-only CLI module so `src/cli/program/helpers.ts` remains free of runtime Commander imports\n- cover invalid and valid limit parsing through the plugins and skills command paths\n\nFixes #84473.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `plugins search --limit` and `skills search --limit` no longer accept partially numeric values such as `1abc`; invalid values fail during CLI option parsing before ClawHub calls, while strict positive integers such as `+1` are still accepted.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS, branch `fix/84473-search-limit-parser`, commit `80c08226f0d96f9d7436da20822cdf6354c6983d`, Node v24.11.1.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran the source-entry CLI parser directly with invalid and valid plugin/skill search limits.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Copied terminal output from the local source checkout:\n\n```console\n$ node --import tsx src/entry.ts plugins search calendar --limit 1abc --json\nOpenClaw could not parse this command: option '--limit <n>' argument '1abc' is invalid. Expected a positive integer.\nTry: openclaw plugins search --help\nexit=1\n\n$ node --import tsx src/entry.ts skills search calendar --limit 1abc --json\nOpenClaw could not parse this command: option '--limit <n>' argument '1abc' is invalid. Expected a positive integer.\nTry: openclaw skills search --help\nexit=1\n\n$ node --import tsx src/entry.ts plugins search calendar --limit +1 --json\n{\n  \"results\": []\n}\nexit=0\n\n$ node --import tsx src/entry.ts skills search calendar --limit +1 --json\n{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"score\": 4.397586954646213,\n      \"slug\": \"calendar\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Calendar\",\n      \"summary\": \"Calendar management and scheduling. Create events, manage meetings, and sync across calendar providers.\",\n      \"version\": null,\n      \"ownerHandle\": \"ndcccccc\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\nexit=0\n```\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/program/helpers.test.ts src/cli/plugins-cli.lazy.test.ts src/cli/skills-cli.commands.test.ts` (3 files, 72 tests passed)\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/cli/program/helpers.ts src/cli/positive-integer-option.ts src/cli/plugins-cli.ts src/cli/skills-cli.ts src/cli/program/helpers.test.ts src/cli/plugins-cli.lazy.test.ts src/cli/skills-cli.commands.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`",
        "branch": "fix/84473-search-limit-parser",
